.TH r-doc 3
.XI r-doc - "R documentation manual page viewer"
.XI .r-doc.rscript 5 "Rscript Command line path" variable|shell
.SH NAME
.Me "|r-doc"
r-doc \- R documentation manual page viewer.
.br
.Me "|.r-doc.rscript"
\&.r-doc.rscript \- Rscript Command line path
.Me $a
.SH SYNOPSIS
.na
\fBr-doc\fR
.br
\fBr-doc\fR \fIfunction\fR
.br
\fBr-doc\fR \fIpackage::packagename\fR
.br
\fBr-doc\fR \fIpackage::function\fR
.br
\fB.r-doc.rscript\fR \fIstring\fR
.ad
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBr-doc\fR  provides  a  mechanism  to display a R manual  page  within the
MicroEmacs  window. On invoking \fBr-doc\fR the user is prompted for the name of
the manual page to display:-
.CS
R help on ?
.CE
The name of the R manual page are entered on the command line.
The macro invokes the R \fBhelp\fR function using the 
.Hr Rscript 1
command  interpreter  which  must be on the  PATH to  generate  the  page  and
display   the  result  in a window.  The Rscript page
executable may be defined with the variable
.B .r-doc.rscript
this is  defined  as  \fCRscript\fR  by default  and should  work on any Linux
system. On Windows the user should point this variable to the Rscript interpreter
within the program files directory.
.PP
Another  R documentation page can be selected by either  moving the cursor to the link
and pressing return or double clicking on it with the left mouse button. \*(mS
will then attempt to load and display the selected R manual page.
.SH NOTES
\fBr-doc\fR is a macro defined in \fChkr.emf\fR.
.PP
.B r-doc
should work mainly within \s-1UNIX\s0  environments but should work as well on
Windows if the 
.B Rscript 
executable is on the PATH or if the user sets the 
.B .r-doc.rscript 
variable.
